In the second interval \(2 \le x \le 4\), the function \(f(x) = 8 - 2x\) is a linear function that decreases as \(x\) increases. Hence, the maximum value in this interval occurs at \(x = 2\): \[f(2) = 8 - 2 \cdot 2 = 4.\]
By comparing the values from both intervals, we see that the maximum value of the function is \(\boxed{4}\). </think> <answer>4</answer>

